value.0: The old castellan glances up at you. "What do you be needing now, <Mister/Missus> <LastName>?"
The old man shuffles up to you with a gleam in his eye. "And do you think you belong in the castle on this <day/night>? Do you have business with the guilds?"
"Even if you were, and I know damn well you are not, I'm too old to go bowing down to any <lord/lady>. I am the castellan, so it is my business to know everything that happens in the Guildhall."
"This is my business, you impertinent upstart. I am the castellan and everything that happens within the Guildhall is my business."
He grunts and nods his head. "I guess I've heard of you. If you have any questions about the keep... figure it out yourself."
"I guess if you're too thick to figure something out, I'm the castellan, so I'll answer."
"That's really too bad, cause I promise you, my answers won't be helpful."
"It's about time. Now, I have a keep to run, so if you don't mind..."
"And you are possibly going to be my new <lord/lady>? Gods help us all, cause you certainly won't."
"I know I look like the muscle-bound, adventurous type, but looks can be deceiving. I actually spend most of my days and nights locked up here in the castle, pretending to work."
"So you'll just have to excuse me if I can't tell you who has the best prices on ladies' undergarments, or where the tastiest ale is served. I haven't had a pint of ale in twenty two years!"
"Rooms, I suspect. Unless someone went and knocked out all the walls. Maybe you should go and check. Take a mop and a bucket with you and clean the floors while you’re at it."
"What do I care? Everyone thinks this damn election is so important, but I tell you, life goes on. You think you're all-fired important one minute, then *WHACK* Mistress Death knocks your skull in."
"And what have you got to show for all your years of effort and toil, a bad back, poor eyesight and goiter the size of a mace head! So you can keep your election and stuff it up your... shirt."
"Well now, the Guildmasters can huff and puff and delay all they want but, when it comes right down to it, I suppose I can call it whenever I darn well please, can't I..."

"The only thing I can't do is stop it once I've started. None of those recount shenanigans, understand? If you lose, you lose; no sense in crying over it. So what do you say? Would you like me to call it?"
"It's all the same to me. Now was there something else you wanted? I honestly can't remember."

"Up and at 'em, everyone! We're having us an election. Why? Because I say so, that's why, you little whippersnappers! All right, <FullName>, I'll go gather the votes and tally the results. Don't make me regret this."
"I make sure everything in the keep runs smoothly, from the servants up to the guild masters, all fall within my responsibility."
"When there is a guild vote, I tally the votes. When a servant retires, I hire a new one."
"I'll forget you said that."

"No seriously... my mind isn't what it used to be. I will forget you said anything, so there is no point in bribing me, cause when it comes time for the vote, I won't remember what I was supposed to do."
"All I do is count the votes. You can give me all the gold you like, but it won't do you a lick of good."
"The guilds have voted. I have tallied the votes and here are the results."
"<CUSTOM6002> votes for Sir Becket."
"<CUSTOM6001> votes for Enivid."
"<CUSTOM6003> votes for <FirstName>."
"Why do politicians never make up their minds? A three way tie! Now, where did I put that law book on elections... ah ha! Here it is!"
"In case of a tie, the castellan will cast the final and deciding vote. What?!? Like I want to make *that* decision! Dang it all, I will just flip a coin!"
"Oh, um... I guess that doesn't really work with three of you."
"Do you have a three-sided coin, Mykes?"
"There is a very simple solution to that... Sir Becket has always been very rude to me, treating me like an overrated slave."
"Come now, Mykes, it was all in good fun! Right?"
"You are out of the running, which leaves me with just <FirstName> and Enivid to worry about. Hmm, I think I will just flip a coin."
He looks at each of the candidates with a challenging gaze. "And nobody gets to challenge this decision!"
"What? You cannot just flip a coin! Just choose me, you imbecilic, senile... er... Mikey, old chap. Please?"

"No, the texts are quite clear! I get the final vote, and since I could really care less who gets the job, I will flip a coin. Heads, <FirstName>. Tails, Enivid. Now where did I place my coin purse... "
"Why do politicians never make up their minds? It would appear we have a tie between Becket and Enivid. Now, where did I put that law book on elections... ah ha! Here it is!"
"Why do politicians never make up their minds? It would appear we have a tie between Enivid and <FirstName>. Now, where did I put that law book on elections... ah ha! Here it is!"

"Very well, who would you choose to be your Banner, then?"
